measures.name: aedg_k_12_electric_equipment_controls
measures.description: This measure reduces the values associated with electric equipment schedules to simulate reductions due to equipment controls throughout the building. This includes occupancy based outlets or adapters, as well as network or timer based controls. Kitchen equipment controls are not altered by this measure. The kitchen has a dedicated measure of its own which includes equipment controls.
measures.modeler_description: This measure is intended to be used on schedules that have not previously been adjusted for advanced controls. If you run this measure multiple times you will end up with more schedule reduction than is appropriate. The schedules used in the OpenStudio templates have not been adjusted for advanced controls, so it is appropriate to run them through this measure to simulation their impact on energy use. This measure applies a reduction of 0.15 to schedule values that are below 0.5 start with, no reduction is applied to values that are at or above 0.5 to start with. As a result the lower the initial fractional value the higher the percentage reduction it will receive. Values won't be lowered to a value below 0.1. Values already below this level will keep their original value.

measures.name: zedgk_12_exterior_wall_construction
measures.description: ZEDG version, currently only set for steel frame walls. This measure will modify existing exterior wall insulation levels based on construction type and climate zone. The exterior wall construction type and climate zone should be set in the model prior to using this measure. For mass and metal walls if an existing insulation layer can be found it will be increased, if not a new insulation layer will be added. For mass this will be at the exterior of the construction. For metal it will be added just behind the exterior layer. For steel and wood framed walls, insulation will be added to the exterior of the construction.

measures.name: net_zero_k_12_fenestration_and_daylighting_controls
measures.display_name: Net Zero K12 - Fenestration and Daylighting Controls
measures.description: This measure will remove all existing exterior windows, glass doors, and skylights from your model. They will be replaced with view and daylight windows as recommended by the Net Zero K12 recommendations. Windows on the south facade will have a exterior shading or light shelf surfaces depending on if they are view or daylight windows. East and west view windows will have internal shading controls. In spaces with daylighting controls daylight sensor will be added. The modeler should inspect where the sensors were placed, the recommended illuminance setpoint, and the fraction of the zones lighting controlled by the sensor.
measures.modeler_description: This measure is intended for use in models created form space types defined in the primary and secondary building types. Other space types used in the model will not receive any new fenestration, however fenestration will be removed from all space types. Attic and plenum spaces will not receive any new fenestration. Daylighting will only be added to north and south facades. North and south facades can be +/- 30 degrees of north and south. East and west facades will only receive view windows. Mechanical rooms won't relieve any view or daylight windows. Kitchens and Restrooms wont' receive any view windows. Toplighting will not be added.In sidelight spaces the sensor's depth in from the wall will typically be the same as the height of the wall that the daylight windows is on. This depth is also what is used to calculate the daylight fraction of the space. In spaces that are non convex, such as an L shaped space, we may not be able to place a sensor, if that happens a warning will be issued.

arguments.option_2: Option 2 Description: This measure will remove all existing exterior windows, glass doors, and skylights from your model. They will be replaced with view and daylight windows as recommended by the Net Zero K12 recommendations. Windows on the south facade will have a exterior shading or light shelf surfaces depending on if they are view or daylight windows. East and west view windows will have internal shading controls. In spaces with daylighting controls daylight sensor will be added. The modeler should inspect where the sensors were placed, the recommended illuminance setpoint, and the fraction of the zones lighting controlled by the sensor.

measures.name: aedg_k_12_exterior_lighting
measures.description: This measure will create exterior lights objects in four different categories described below. The lighting levels and controls will be based on the "How to Implement Recommendations" section in the AEDG; any existing exterior lighting will be removed. A special input is needed for this measure to define the exterior lighting zone, which further describes whether the site is urban or rural.
measures.modeler_description:
Provide an area or dimensions as input for each of the exterior lighting categories described below. 
- Facade and landscape lighting
- Parking lots and drives
- Walkways, plaza, and special features areas
- All other exterior lighting
    
Lighting Zones:
0 - Undeveloped areas within national parks, state parks, forest land, rural areas, and other undeveloped areas as defined by the authority having jurisdiction (no lighting recommendations)
1 - Developed areas of national parks, state parks, forest land, and rural areas (no lighting recommendations)
2 - Areas predominantly consisting of residential zoning, neighborhood business districts, light industrial with limited nighttime use and residential mixed use areas
3 - All other areas
4 - High activity commercial districts in major metropolitan areas as designated by the local jurisdiction

measures.name: net_zero_k_12_hvac
measures.description: todo - updat edescription. Measure replaces existing HVAC system (if any) with a Ground Source Heat Pump (GSHP) with DOAS HVAC system (one DOAS per floor).  The GSHP with DOAS system (centralized DOAS, with zone level conditioning) is applied to all space types except Cafeteria, Kitchen, Gym, and Auditorium; packaged single zone equipment is applied to those zones.  In select cases, the user is given the option to preserve existing HVAC schedules.  In other cases, new schedules are generated that align with AEDG recommendations.  The resulting HVAC system reflects the HVAC recommendations of the 50% K-12 AEDG.
measures.modeler_description: Airloops are dedicated to ventilation (DOAS) and have variable speed fan operation and hot and chilled water coils.  Chiller for DOAS is air-cooled.  Conditioning is provided at the zone level with water sourced heat pumps with cycling fans.  The heat pumps are connected to a plant loop supplied by district heating and cooling.  The district heating and cooling approximate the performance of a (optimally-sized) ground loop.  The heat pump loop floats between 5 C and 21 C.  Currently, district heating and cooling energy is not removed from EnergyPlus results.  Packaged single zone systems have constant speed fan operation, gas furnace heating, and single speed DX cooling.

measures.description: This measure is meant to be paired with the Net Zero K12 HVAC measure to add EMS in place of a ground source loop.
measures.modeler_description: This measure will get the last OSM and then find the inlet node for the Plant component Temperature Source object. It will then create EMS to schedule the temperature.

arguments.option_1: GSHP Plant Component Temp Source EMS

options.name: GSHP Plant Component Temp Source EMS
options.description: Option 1 Description

measures.name: openstudio_results
measures.description: This measure creates high level tables and charts pulling both from model inputs and EnergyPlus results. It has building level information as well as detail on space types, thermal zones, HVAC systems, envelope characteristics, and economics. Click the heading above a chart to view a table of the chart data.
measures.modeler_description: For the most part consumption data comes from the tabular EnergyPlus results, however there are a few requests added for time series results. Space type and loop details come from the OpenStudio model. The code for this is modular, making it easy to use as a template for your own custom reports. The structure of the report uses bootstrap, and the graphs use dimple js.

options.name: Results
options.description: Option 1 Description

measures.name: envelope_and_internal_load_breakdown
measures.description: Report provides annual and monthly views into heat gains and losses for envelope and internal loads.
measures.modeler_description: It uses the following variables: Electric Equipment Total Heating Energy, Zone Lights Total Heating Energy, Zone, People Sensible Heating Energy, Surface Average Face Conduction Heat Transfer Energy, Surface Window Heat Gain Energy, Surface Window Heat Loss Energy, Zone Infiltration Sensible Heat Gain Energy, Zone Infiltration Sensible Heat Loss Energy. For Surface Average Face Conduction Heat Transfer Energy bin positive values as heat gain and negative values as heat loss.

arguments.option_1: Option 1 Description: Report provides annual and monthly views into heat gains and losses for envelope and internal loads.

da_descriptions.name: ZEDG Elec Equip
da_descriptions.description: Option 1 Description: Customized values for ZEDG - This measure removes all existing electric equipment from spaces recognized as primary or secondary school space types. One exception is that loads assigned directly to a space whre the load definition contains "Elev" or "elev" will be left alone. New electric equipment will be added based on the 50% K12 AEDG recommendations. Kitchen equipment wont' be altered by this measure. There is a stand alone AEDG measure specifically for the kitchen.

da_descriptions.description: Option 1 Description

da_descriptions.name: ZEDG Ext Wall
da_descriptions.description: Option 1 Description: ZEDG version, currently only set for steel frame walls. This measure will modify existing exterior wall insulation levels based on construction type and climate zone. The exterior wall construction type and climate zone should be set in the model prior to using this measure. For mass and metal walls if an existing insulation layer can be found it will be increased, if not a new insulation layer will be added. For mass this will be at the exterior of the construction. For metal it will be added just behind the exterior layer. For steel and wood framed walls, insulation will be added to the exterior of the construction.

da_descriptions.name: ZEDG Roof
da_descriptions.description: Option 1 Description: ZEDG version, only setup for IEAD roof. This measure will modify existing roof insulation levels and Solar Reflective Index (SRI) values based on roof type and climate zone. The roof type and climate zone should be set in the model prior to using this measure. If your model uses an attic, all attic surfaces should have an "Attic' intended surface type. For attics it doesn't matter what you put for "Standards Construction Type". The measure will check attic insulation where the attic is adjacent to other not attic spaces.

da_descriptions.name: AEDG Int Finishes
da_descriptions.description: Option 1 Description

da_descriptions.name: ZEDG Fenistration with Daylighting
da_descriptions.description: Option 2 Description: This measure will remove all existing exterior windows, glass doors, and skylights from your model. They will be replaced with view and daylight windows as recommended by the Net Zero K12 recommendations. Windows on the south facade will have a exterior shading or light shelf surfaces depending on if they are view or daylight windows. East and west view windows will have internal shading controls. In spaces with daylighting controls daylight sensor will be added. The modeler should inspect where the sensors were placed, the recommended illuminance setpoint, and the fraction of the zones lighting controlled by the sensor.

da_descriptions.name: net_zero_k_12_hvac
da_descriptions.description: todo - updat edescription. Measure replaces existing HVAC system (if any) with a Ground Source Heat Pump (GSHP) with DOAS HVAC system (one DOAS per floor).  The GSHP with DOAS system (centralized DOAS, with zone level conditioning) is applied to all space types except Cafeteria, Kitchen, Gym, and Auditorium; packaged single zone equipment is applied to those zones.  In select cases, the user is given the option to preserve existing HVAC schedules.  In other cases, new schedules are generated that align with AEDG recommendations.  The resulting HVAC system reflects the HVAC recommendations of the 50% K-12 AEDG.

da_descriptions.name: ZEDG VRF
da_descriptions.description: Option 1 Description: Custom ZEDG measure based on generic VRF with DOAS measure.

da_descriptions.name: zedg_k_12_hvac_fan_coil_doas_air_cooled_chiller
da_descriptions.description: Custom version of AEDG K12 HVAC Fan Coil DOAS adjusted for use with ZEDG. Measure replaces existing HVAC system (if any) with a Fan Coil with DOAS HVAC with air cooled Chiller system (one DOAS per floor).  The fan coil with DOAS system (centralized DOAS, with zone level conditioning) is applied to all space types except Cafeteria, Kitchen, Gym, and Auditorium; packaged single zone equipment is applied to those zones.  In select cases, the user is given the option to preserve existing HVAC schedules.  In other cases, new schedules are generated that align with AEDG recommendations.  The resulting HVAC system reflects the HVAC recommendations of the 50% K-12 AEDG.

steps.description: Option 1 Description: ZEDG version, currently only set for steel frame walls. This measure will modify existing exterior wall insulation levels based on construction type and climate zone. The exterior wall construction type and climate zone should be set in the model prior to using this measure. For mass and metal walls if an existing insulation layer can be found it will be increased, if not a new insulation layer will be added. For mass this will be at the exterior of the construction. For metal it will be added just behind the exterior layer. For steel and wood framed walls, insulation will be added to the exterior of the construction.
steps.name: ZEDG Ext Wall

This measure will modify existing roof insulation levels and Solar Reflective Index (SRI) values based on roof type and climate zone. The roof type and climate zone should be set in the model prior to using this measure. If your model uses an attic, all attic surfaces should have an "Attic' intended surface type. For attics it doesn't matter what you put for "Standards Construction Type". The measure will check attic insulation where the attic is adjacent to other not attic spaces.

steps.description: Option 2 Description: This measure will remove all existing exterior windows, glass doors, and skylights from your model. They will be replaced with view and daylight windows as recommended by the Net Zero K12 recommendations. Windows on the south facade will have a exterior shading or light shelf surfaces depending on if they are view or daylight windows. East and west view windows will have internal shading controls. In spaces with daylighting controls daylight sensor will be added. The modeler should inspect where the sensors were placed, the recommended illuminance setpoint, and the fraction of the zones lighting controlled by the sensor.
steps.name: ZEDG Fenistration with Daylighting

steps.description: todo - updat edescription. Measure replaces existing HVAC system (if any) with a Ground Source Heat Pump (GSHP) with DOAS HVAC system (one DOAS per floor).  The GSHP with DOAS system (centralized DOAS, with zone level conditioning) is applied to all space types except Cafeteria, Kitchen, Gym, and Auditorium; packaged single zone equipment is applied to those zones.  In select cases, the user is given the option to preserve existing HVAC schedules.  In other cases, new schedules are generated that align with AEDG recommendations.  The resulting HVAC system reflects the HVAC recommendations of the 50% K-12 AEDG.
steps.name: net_zero_k_12_hvac

steps.description: Custom version of AEDG K12 HVAC Fan Coil DOAS adjusted for use with ZEDG. Measure replaces existing HVAC system (if any) with a Fan Coil with DOAS HVAC with air cooled Chiller system (one DOAS per floor).  The fan coil with DOAS system (centralized DOAS, with zone level conditioning) is applied to all space types except Cafeteria, Kitchen, Gym, and Auditorium; packaged single zone equipment is applied to those zones.  In select cases, the user is given the option to preserve existing HVAC schedules.  In other cases, new schedules are generated that align with AEDG recommendations.  The resulting HVAC system reflects the HVAC recommendations of the 50% K-12 AEDG.

da_descriptions.name: Aurora CO
da_descriptions.description: Option 12 Description: Change the building location

da_descriptions.name: ZEDG Elec Equip
da_descriptions.description: Option 1 Description: Customized values for ZEDG - This measure removes all existing electric equipment from spaces recognized as primary or secondary school space types. One exception is that loads assigned directly to a space whre the load definition contains "Elev" or "elev" will be left alone. New electric equipment will be added based on the 50% K12 AEDG recommendations. Kitchen equipment wont' be altered by this measure. There is a stand alone AEDG measure specifically for the kitchen.

da_descriptions.name: AEDG Elec Equip Controls
da_descriptions.description: Option 1 Description

da_descriptions.name: ZEDG Int Lighting
da_descriptions.description: Option 1 Description

da_descriptions.name: AEDG Int Lighting Controls
da_descriptions.description: Option 1 Description

da_descriptions.name: ZEDG Ext Wall
da_descriptions.description: Option 1 Description: ZEDG version, currently only set for steel frame walls. This measure will modify existing exterior wall insulation levels based on construction type and climate zone. The exterior wall construction type and climate zone should be set in the model prior to using this measure. For mass and metal walls if an existing insulation layer can be found it will be increased, if not a new insulation layer will be added. For mass this will be at the exterior of the construction. For metal it will be added just behind the exterior layer. For steel and wood framed walls, insulation will be added to the exterior of the construction.

da_descriptions.name: ZEDG Roof
da_descriptions.description: Option 1 Description: ZEDG version, only setup for IEAD roof. This measure will modify existing roof insulation levels and Solar Reflective Index (SRI) values based on roof type and climate zone. The roof type and climate zone should be set in the model prior to using this measure. If your model uses an attic, all attic surfaces should have an "Attic' intended surface type. For attics it doesn't matter what you put for "Standards Construction Type". The measure will check attic insulation where the attic is adjacent to other not attic spaces.

da_descriptions.name: AEDG Int Finishes
da_descriptions.description: Option 1 Description

da_descriptions.name: ZEDG Fenistration with Daylighting
da_descriptions.description: Option 2 Description: This measure will remove all existing exterior windows, glass doors, and skylights from your model. They will be replaced with view and daylight windows as recommended by the Net Zero K12 recommendations. Windows on the south facade will have a exterior shading or light shelf surfaces depending on if they are view or daylight windows. East and west view windows will have internal shading controls. In spaces with daylighting controls daylight sensor will be added. The modeler should inspect where the sensors were placed, the recommended illuminance setpoint, and the fraction of the zones lighting controlled by the sensor.

da_descriptions.name: ZEDG SWH Secondary
da_descriptions.description: Option 2 Description: Todo - update this to use electric. Measure replaces existing swh equipment (if any) with the swh equipment recommendations of the 50% K-12 AEDG.

da_descriptions.name: Kitchen ZEDG Secondary
da_descriptions.description: Option 2 Description: Todo - update this to use electric. Measure replaces existing kitchen equipment (if any) with refrigeration, electric, and gas equipment that align with the kitchen equipment recommendations of the 50% K-12 AEDG.

da_descriptions.name: zedg_k_12_hvac_fan_coil_doas_air_cooled_chiller
da_descriptions.description: Custom version of AEDG K12 HVAC Fan Coil DOAS adjusted for use with ZEDG. Measure replaces existing HVAC system (if any) with a Fan Coil with DOAS HVAC with air cooled Chiller system (one DOAS per floor).  The fan coil with DOAS system (centralized DOAS, with zone level conditioning) is applied to all space types except Cafeteria, Kitchen, Gym, and Auditorium; packaged single zone equipment is applied to those zones.  In select cases, the user is given the option to preserve existing HVAC schedules.  In other cases, new schedules are generated that align with AEDG recommendations.  The resulting HVAC system reflects the HVAC recommendations of the 50% K-12 AEDG.

steps.description: Custom version of AEDG K12 HVAC Fan Coil DOAS adjusted for use with ZEDG. Measure replaces existing HVAC system (if any) with a Fan Coil with DOAS HVAC with air cooled Chiller system (one DOAS per floor).  The fan coil with DOAS system (centralized DOAS, with zone level conditioning) is applied to all space types except Cafeteria, Kitchen, Gym, and Auditorium; packaged single zone equipment is applied to those zones.  In select cases, the user is given the option to preserve existing HVAC schedules.  In other cases, new schedules are generated that align with AEDG recommendations.  The resulting HVAC system reflects the HVAC recommendations of the 50% K-12 AEDG.

da_descriptions.name: zedgvrf_with_doas
da_descriptions.description: Custom ZEDG measure based on generic VRF with DOAS measure.

da_descriptions.name: ZEDG Fan Coil Air Cooled Chiller
da_descriptions.description: Option 1 Description: Custom version of AEDG K12 HVAC Fan Coil DOAS adjusted for use with ZEDG. Measure replaces existing HVAC system (if any) with a Fan Coil with DOAS HVAC with air cooled Chiller system (one DOAS per floor).  The fan coil with DOAS system (centralized DOAS, with zone level conditioning) is applied to all space types except Cafeteria, Kitchen, Gym, and Auditorium; packaged single zone equipment is applied to those zones.  In select cases, the user is given the option to preserve existing HVAC schedules.  In other cases, new schedules are generated that align with AEDG recommendations.  The resulting HVAC system reflects the HVAC recommendations of the 50% K-12 AEDG.

steps.description: Option 1 Description: ZEDG version, currently only set for steel frame walls. This measure will modify existing exterior wall insulation levels based on construction type and climate zone. The exterior wall construction type and climate zone should be set in the model prior to using this measure. For mass and metal walls if an existing insulation layer can be found it will be increased, if not a new insulation layer will be added. For mass this will be at the exterior of the construction. For metal it will be added just behind the exterior layer. For steel and wood framed walls, insulation will be added to the exterior of the construction.

steps.description: todo - updat edescription. Measure replaces existing HVAC system (if any) with a Ground Source Heat Pump (GSHP) with DOAS HVAC system (one DOAS per floor).  The GSHP with DOAS system (centralized DOAS, with zone level conditioning) is applied to all space types except Cafeteria, Kitchen, Gym, and Auditorium; packaged single zone equipment is applied to those zones.  In select cases, the user is given the option to preserve existing HVAC schedules.  In other cases, new schedules are generated that align with AEDG recommendations. steps.description: Option 1 Description: Custom version of AEDG K12 HVAC Fan Coil DOAS adjusted for use with ZEDG. In select cases, the user is given the option to preserve existing HVAC schedules.  In other cases, new schedules are generated that align with AEDG recommendations.
